<br>
If you've ever backed out of range of a perma-rooted mob while full health, and been summoned back repeatedly while every other melee in the guild was in range, that should tell you that proximity isn't all that important. If you have good aggro, proximity doesn't matter. If you don't, well I guess every little bit helps. <br>
<br>
It's very mob specific of course, AoW (and most stuff in kael) is very much proximity based. On the other hand, Arch Lich, Creator, Cursed, High priest etc. don't seem to care how far away you are as long as you're in melee range. I've tanked them all from further away than people he was ignoring plenty of times, because of knockback/stun, positioning, or whatever else.<br>
